==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crocket
<hw>Crock"et</hw> <pr>(kr?k"?t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>croquet</ets>, F. <ets>crochet</ets>, dim. of <ets>croc</ets> hook.
See <er>Crook</er>, and cf. <er>Crotchet</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>An ornament often resembling curved and bent
foliage, projecting from the sloping edge of a gable, spire,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A croche, or knob, on the top of a stag's
antler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The antlers and the <qex>crockets</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Black.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crocketed</ent>⟦br⟧
